     \end {tikzcd}


 Thus \top  f classifies 1_x, so that f is unique since \top  is
   monic and (by the previous paragraph) characteristic maps are unique.

Analogously to the construction of the unit of an adjunction, this equivalently
means there is a map c\xrightarrow {\eta _c} Ud in C (the transpose of 1_d),
called a universal arrow to U, such that for any z\in  D, any map
x\xrightarrow {f} Uz admits a unique lift to a map d\xrightarrow {g} z in D factoring
through \eta _x:





